<h3>Really, really small pictures</h3>
<div class="story">
   <p>A fascinating (if you are an engineer) look at pictures that have been engraved on to commercial integrated circuits amongst the &quot;wires&quot; and transistors.  Most are only a fraction of a millimeter across. The pyramid at right showing the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_Seal_of_the_United_States" target="_blank" class="external">Great Seal of the United States</a> is just one example. You can waste a lot of time here.</p>
